        <updateDate>2023-11-13T19:31:36Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Freeing Americans Detained Abroad Act&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal;"&gt;This bill requires the Department of State to dedicate resources to assist U.S. citizens detained or kidnapped overseas. The State Department must&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;display, on a public website, a list of resources (including legal services offered pro bono or with payment) that U.S. citizens detained or kidnapped overseas may be eligible to receive;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;train all Foreign Service officers posted overseas on identifying and assisting detained and arbitrarily detained U.S. citizens; and&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;designate at least one Foreign Service officer at each overseas diplomatic or consular post as a hostage affairs officer. &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
